SIMPLE: pause
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pause
<hw>Pause</hw> <pr>(p⟦add⟧z)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr. L.
<ets>pausa</ets>. See <er>Pose</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A temporary
stop or rest; an intermission of action; interruption; suspension;
cessation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Temporary inaction or waiting; hesitation; suspence;
doubt.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I stand in <qex>pause</qex> where I shall first begin.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>In speaking or reading aloud, a brief arrest or
suspension of voice, to indicate the limits and relations of sentences
and their parts.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>In writing and printing, a mark indicating the place
and nature of an arrest of voice in reading; a punctuation point;
<as>as, teach the pupil to mind the <ex>pauses</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>A break or paragraph in writing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He writes with warmth, which usually neglects method, and those
partitions and <qex>pauses</qex> which men educated in schools
observe.</q> <rj><qau>Locke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>6.</sn> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>A hold. See 4th <er>Hold</er>,
7.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Stop; cessation; suspension.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pause</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Pause
<hw>Pause</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Paused</conjf> <pr>(p⟦add⟧zd)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Pausing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf. F. <ets>pauser</ets>, L.
<ets>pausare</ets>. See <er>Pause</er>, <pos>n.</pos>,
<er>Pose</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To make a short stop; to cease
for a time; to intermit speaking or acting; to stop; to wait; to
rest.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Tarry, <xex>pause</xex> a day or two.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Pausing</qex> a while, thus to herself she mused.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To be intermitted; to cease; <as>as, the music
<ex>pauses</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To hesitate; to hold back; to delay.</def>
<rj><mark>[R.]</mark></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Why doth the Jew <qex>pause</qex>? Take thy forfeiture.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj> <-- is this anti-semitic or what? -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>To stop in order to consider; hence, to consider; to
reflect.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧Take time to
<xex>pause</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To pause upon</b></col>, <cd>to deliberate
concerning.</cd> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To intermit; stop; stay; wait; delay; tarry;
hesitate; demur.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pause</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Pause
<hw>Pause</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To cause to stop or rest; -- used
reflexively.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pauser</ent>⟦br⟧
